LocPromotionPopupText = "Use Energy to reanimate a nearby dead humanoid to fight for you as a Zombie:<br/><br/><font color='#CA7200'>Base Effects:</font> (<font color='#c451c2'><Ability:REANIMATE_FOCUS_COST/> Energy</font>)<br/><Bullet/> Raise a Zombie that begins with 1 action immediately after spawning.<br/><br/><font color='#CA7200'>Empowered Effects:</font> (<font color='#c451c2'><Ability:REANIMATE_EMPOWERED_FOCUS_COST/> Energy</font>)<br/><Bullet/> The raised Zombie is empowered, gaining additional Health, Dodge, and Mobility.<br/><Bullet/> The raised Zombie begins with 2 actions immediately after spawning.<br/><br/>NOTES:<br/><Bullet/> Reanimated Zombies have a dashing-melee claw attack that may be used with movement.<br/><Bullet/> Reanimated Zombies will not be affected when their linked Templar is impaired, but will be killed if their linked Templar is removed from play (killed, evaced, etc.).<br/><Bullet/> Eligible bodies must be within <font color='#CA7200'><Ability:REANIMATE_TILE_RANGE/></font> Tiles to be reanimated - the range will be shown when selecting the ability.<br/><Bullet/> The number Zombies that a Templar can maintain at once is limited to: <font color='#CA7200'><Ability:REANIMATE_ZOMBIE_LIMIT/></font>. <br/><Bullet/> Reanimating a Zombie will always break squad concealment."

